caption.center: Alberine KELLY, Appellant, v. The STATE of Texas, Appellee

court.center: Court of Criminal Appeals of Texas.

opinion.posture: Appeal from the County Court, Dawson County, Aubrey Boswell, J.
opinion.attorneys: Leon Douglas, State's Atty., Austin, for the State.Page 277
opinion.opinion_text:
The offense is the unlawful sale of whiskey in a dry area; the punishment, a fine of $100.
The record on appeal contains no statement of facts or bills of exception. All proceedings appear to be regular, and nothing is presented for review.
The judgment is affirmed, and no motion for rehearing will be entertained in this appeal.
